\pard\s1\sb240\sa120{\b\fs44 {\rtlch\f1 \fs52 Demonstration of DOCX support in}}\par
\pard\s1\sb240\sa120{\b\fs44 {\rtlch\f1 \fs52 calibre}}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 This document demonstrates the ability of the calibre DOCX Input plugin to}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 convert the various typographic features in a Microsoft Word (2007 and newer)}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 document. Convert this document to a modern ebook format, such as AZW3 for}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Kindles or EPUB for other ebook readers, to see it in action.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 There is support for images, tables, lists, footnotes, endnotes, links, dropcaps and}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 various types of text and paragraph level formatting.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 To see the DOCX conversion in action, simply add this file to calibre using the}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 \u8220?Add Books\u8221? button and then click \u8220? Convert\u8221?. Set the output format in the top right}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 corner of the conversion dialog to EPUB or AZW3 and click \u8220?OK\u8221? .}\par
\pard\s5\sb240\sa120{\b\fs28 {\rtlch\f1 \fs28 Text Formatting}}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs26 Inline formatting}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Here, we demonstrate various types of inline text formatting and the use of}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 embedded fonts.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Here is some }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 bold, italic, bold-italic, }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 underlined and struck out text. Then, we}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 have a super }{\rtlch\f1 \fs16 script }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 and a sub }{\rtlch\f1 \fs16 script }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 . Now we see some red, green and blue text. Some text}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 with a yellow highlight. Some text in a box. Some text in inverse video.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 A paragraph with styled text: }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 subtle emphasis }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 followed by }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 strong text }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 and}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 intense emphasis }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 . This paragraph uses document wide styles for styling rather than}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 inline text properties as demonstrated in the previous paragraph \u8212? calibre can handle}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 both with equal ease.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs26 Fun with fonts}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 This document has embedded the Ubuntu font family. The body text is in the}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Ubuntu typeface, here is }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 some text in the Ubuntu Mono typeface, notice how every}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 letter has the same width, even i and m }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 . Every embedded font will automatically}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 be embedded in the output ebook during conversion.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs26 Paragraph level formatting}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 You can do crazy things with paragraphs, if the urge strikes you. For instance this}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 paragraph is right aligned and has a right border. It has also been given a light gray}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 background.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 For the lovers of poetry amongst you, paragraphs with hanging indents, like this often}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 come in handy. You can use hanging indents to ensure that a line of poetry}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 retains its individual identity as a line even when the screen is too narrow to}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 display it as a single line. Not only does this paragraph have a hanging indent, it}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 is also has an extra top margin, setting it apart from the preceding paragraph.}\par
\pard\s5\sb240\sa120{\b\fs28 {\rtlch\f1 \b \fs28 Tables\b0 }}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \b \fs22 ITEM NEEDED \b0 }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Tables in Word can vary from the extremely}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs22 Books 1 }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 simple to the extremely complex. calibre tries to do}\par
