\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 its best when converting tables. While you may run}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs22 Highlighter 2 colors }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 into trouble with the occasional table, the vast}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs22 Scissors 1 pair }{\rtlch\f1 \fs24 majority of common cases should be converted very}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 well, as demonstrated in this section. Note that for}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 optimum results, when creating tables in Word, you should set their widths using}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 percentages, rather than absolute units. To the left of this paragraph is a floating two}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 column table with a nice green border and header row.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Now let\u8217?s look at a fancier table\u8212? one with alternating row colors and partial}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 borders. This table is stretched out to take 100% of the available width.}\par
