\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 Next, we have something a little more complex, a nested table, i.e. a table inside}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 another table. Additionally, the inner table has some of its cells merged. The table is}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 displayed horizontally centered.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs22 One Two To the left is a table inside a}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs22 table, with some cells}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs22 Three Four merged.}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 We end with a fancy calendar, note how much of the original formatting is}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 preserved. Note that this table will only display correctly on relatively wide screens. In}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 general, very wide tables or tables whose cells have fixed width requirements don\u8217?t}\par
\pard\sa120 {\rtlch\f1 \fs24 fare well in ebooks.}\par
